id: pm-wfvq
title: "Torn-install bundle transients block scheduled releases: boot-time chunk-integrity self-check + distinct error code for gate classification"
description: "2026-07-12 scheduled Auto Release (run 29181568390) was blocked by the sentry-telemetry-gate on PM-CLI-26 (SyntaxError: chunk-IV4NIS5E.js missing export verifyHistoryChain, 1 event) and PM-CLI-10 (ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND at module load, 6 events since 05-31). Both are torn-install/torn-build transients on the operator machine: dist/cli-bundle uses hashed esbuild chunks (chunk-XXXX.js), and chunk-IV4NIS5E exists in NO current build — main.js from one build generation resolved chunks from another during a concurrent upgrade/rebuild. Generic 'cannot find module' patterns CANNOT be added to KNOWN_EXPECTED_HANDLED_ENVIRONMENT_ISSUE_PATTERNS (scripts/release/sentry-telemetry-gate.mjs) because real shipped regressions (e.g. the CJS-host DOA P0) present identically. Class fix: (1) emit a build-generation manifest (chunk names + hash) into dist/cli-bundle at build time; (2) at CLI boot, on module-resolution failure inside the bundle, compare manifest vs on-disk chunks and re-raise as a distinct handled error code (e.g. bundle_integrity_torn_install) with a friendly 'partial upgrade detected — reinstall' hint; (3) allowlist ONLY that distinct code in the gate's environment classification; (4) leave genuine module errors blocking. GH-521 is the auto-filed ops alert for the blocked run."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: ci,release,telemetry
created_at: "2026-07-12T06:09:21.399Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T00:29:22.838Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-14T00:29:22.156Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 150
acceptance_criteria: Build emits a chunk manifest; boot-time resolution failures inside dist/cli-bundle are re-raised as a distinct handled bundle-integrity error code with reinstall hint; sentry-telemetry-gate classifies only that code as expected-handled environment noise; regression test proves a genuine missing-module error still blocks the gate; docs note the torn-install signature
parent: pm-u9d0
risk: medium
confidence: high
resolution: "Added an atomic SHA-256 bundle generation manifest, startup integrity diagnosis with bundle_integrity_torn_install, exact-code release-gate classification, and intact-manifest fail-closed behavior."
expected_result: Only manifest-proven partial upgrades receive a handled reinstall diagnostic; genuine missing-module/export regressions keep blocking releases.
actual_result: "Manifest generation, changed/missing/hash-invalid classification, genuine-error blocking, packed install, and live Sentry gate paths all pass."
